column5: Lot of people on the ice this weekend and the bite remained tough.  We still put some fish on the ice, but we had to work for them.  X-Zone Swammers did most of the damage this weekend.           And a video as usual, http://youtu.be/0BuPLhzHZ9U
Awesome steve.How many were naturals?  Ah ,your vid link didnt come up.
Beauty fish Steve. Really nice ones! Thanks for posting.
Anybody would be a happy with a couple of those!!  Great pics.
Just incredible  If that's how many you get when the bite is tough, it boggles the mind how many you'd get when the bite is easy!  Beautiful fish!
Awesome report Steve. Those are some nice lakers. Just wondering how many inches there was out there.
Nice job!! You definitely have them dialed in!!
Nice fish, excellent pix.  Must have been a slippery walk, I don't see any snow at all.  How much ice?
A nice days catch any time there
